tlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/1","description":"The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/open.png","name":"Open","id":"1","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10002","id":"10002","name":"Cloud Controller"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10004","id":"10004","name":"Database"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10010","id":"10010","name":"Node Controller"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10014","id":"10014","name":"Storage Controller"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Eucalyptus EBS is not operator friendly enough and has certain failure modes that are difficult to recover from. EBS includes the front, middle, and backend components (CLC, SC, NC) and the state models, messages, and interfaces between them for managing volumes, snapshots, and attachments.\r\n\r\nAreas of focus:\r\n* SC storage usage - Operator must be able to easily define the capacity of the cluster for EBS and be confident it will not be exceeded. This includes volume, snapshot, and temporary/scratch space used for uploads.\r\n\r\n* CLC<->SC volume state updates - Volumes must never be lost or orphaned. Worst case behavior should allow the admin to remove volumes explicitly. CLC must be able to request volume creation, transition to a failed state if necessary, and asynchronously clean the volumes during the run-instance path\r\n\r\n* Forced state updates - operator must have a way to forcibly flush a volume or snapshot from the system including all attachment state. This must be idempotent and may not be safe, so should be operator/admin only.\r\n\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":nu